title: The Untold Truth Of Alex Trebek's Marriage
tags: nicki swift|nickiswift|alex trebek|alex trebek and jean trebek|alex and jean trebek|jeopardy|jeopardy!|jeopardy host|jeopardy! host|alex trebek wife|alex trebek's wife|untold truth of alex trebek|alex trebek's marriage|alex trebek marriage|truth about alex trebek|alex trebek cancer|alex trebek dying|alex trebek truth|alex trebek untold truth|alex trebek wife truth|alex trebek marriage truth
description: This legendary game show host may have found his match when it comes to romance, but that doesn't mean that his relationship is exactly what you'd expect. Here's the untold truth of Alex Trebek's marriage.Alex Trebek first met New York native Jean Currivan, who was a real estate project manager at the time, at a party in 1988, several years after his divorce from his first wife in 1981. The pair obviously hit it off because Alex decided to take a chance and asked Jean over to dinner at his home. She said yes, but not without a bit of apprehension. She later admitted to People Magazine that she was really nervous about getting involved with Alex, saying,I was afraid I'd mispronounce my own name!Surely most Jeopardy! contestants can relate to that worry! Despite Jean's initial apprehension, she explained that the classy host that contestants meet and the intimidatingly dapper man that viewers at home see is different from the person she went on a date with. As she put it,Alex is really down to earth. He's much more casual than he is on the show. It's Alex's job to be astute, perfect, and articulate on the air. But he certainly doesn't want to be that way at home. People think he goes to bed in a suit. He doesn't.While Jean didn't specify what exactly Alex wears to bed, we would guess it's not an old t-shirt and boxers either. Perhaps he opts for some sophisticated silk pajamas?Alex Trebek is quite a bit older than Jean, who was just 24 when they met and 26 when they got engaged. Alex was already 48 when they were introduced and had turned 50 by the time he proposed. And while celebrity relationships with significant age gaps aren't much of an issue for a lot of couples in the entertainment industry, Jean has admitted that the age difference could've been problematic for her. In January 2019, she told People Magazine,I kept thinking, he's 24 years older than me‚Ä¶but there was something that just kept drawing me to him.Alex also talked to People about the age gap back in 1990, noting,At first it worried me. But then I thought, 'The hell with it. We'll make it work.'Jean added,I can understand why he was cautious about being with a younger woman. So I didn't try to push him. We just took it one day at a time.And eventually, one day at a time led to happily ever after for these two.Although Alex was divorced when he met Jean, that doesn't mean he was living alone, as his mother Lucille was his roommate. Luckily, though, having mom around didn't cramp Alex's style while he was dating. In fact, Lucille was quite accommodating. As Alex explained to People Magazine,If I was entertaining, she'd make herself scarce. She was the same way with Jean.Lucille continued to live with the couple after they got married, which didn't seem to be an issue either. In fact, Alex noted,[Lucille and Jean] get along like a house on fire. They squeeze me out.Jean confirmed that she is indeed fond of her mother-in-law and often spends time with her in the evening when Alex isn't around. Considering all these warm feelings, it's no surprise that Alex got a little choked up while sending his mother a special birthday message during a 2016 episode of Jeopardy!A woman named Lucille, who today celebrates her 95th birthday. Way to go, Ma!Keep watching the video to find out more about the untold truth of Alex Trebek‚Äôs marriage!#AlexTrebek #Jeopardy #CelebCouplesRead Full Article: https://www.nickiswift.com/181390/the-untold-truth-of-alex-trebeks-marriage/Nervous first meeting | 0:12Age gap | 1:24Alex's roommate | 2:19One regret | 3:12Prankster Alex | 4:05Proud parents | 4:56A simple life | 5:52Challenges and beautiful times | 6:50Alternative therapies for Alex | 7:53Finding peace amidst the pain | 8:50

description: Alex Trebek gave a simple yet powerful statement as to what he wanted his legacy to be after the iconic game show host was diagnosed with pancreatic cancer last spring. description: In February of 2017, Senior Video Correspondent Graham Flanagan spent a day behind the scenes of ‚ÄúJeopardy!‚Äù at Sony Pictures Studios in Los Angeles.On March 6, 2019, Alex Trebek, the 78-year-old host of ‚ÄúJeopardy!,‚Äù announced that he has been diagnosed with stage 4 pancreatic cancer. In a video message posted to the long-running game show‚Äôs YouTube channel, Trebek delivered the news with transparency,  humor, and optimism.‚ÄúI plan to beat the low survival rate statistics for this disease,‚Äù Trebek said in the video message. ‚ÄúTruth told, I have to! Because under the terms of my contract, I have to host ‚ÄúJeopardy!‚Äù for three more years!‚ÄùIn addition to being present for the five episodes that were taped that day, Flanagan got to spend a limited amount of one-on-one time with Trebek, who has been hosting the show since 1984.He got an inside look at Trebek‚Äôs pre-show routine, and got the iconic host to open up about his diet, his passion for labor-intensive housework, and the reason he‚Äôs never lost his passion for hosting ‚ÄúJeopardy!‚Äù after more than 7,000 episodes.Flanagan also recorded Trebek‚Äôs interactions with the live studio audience during commercial breaks, wherein he takes unscripted questions. ‚ÄúNo subject is taboo,‚Äù Trebek said.This visit to the ‚ÄúJeopardy!‚Äù set came the day after a category that featured Trebek reciting rap lyrics went viral, making headlines due to his deadpan delivery of verses by artists like Drake and Lil‚Äô Wayne.Business Insider released a series of short videos produced from  the footage captured in 2017. title: One Of Trebek's Last Jeopardy! Moments Will Bring You To Tears
tags: the list|thelist|one of trebek's last jeopardy! moments will bring you to tears|trebek|alex trebek|game show host|game show host alex trebek|jeopardy|jeopardy!|jeopardy host|jeopardy host alex|jeopardy host alex trebek|alex trebek jeopardy|alex trebek jeopardy host|alex trebek host of jeopardy|host of jeopardy alex trebek|jeopardy host alex trebek death|alex trebek death|alex trebek last show|alex trebek last jeopardy game|jeopardy game show
description: As Jeopardy! fans around the world learn of the heartbreaking death of legendary host Alex Trebek, many are taking to social media to share their favorite moments from the show. After manning the helm for a mind-blowing 37 seasons and 8,200 episodes, Trebek gave us plenty of memories and moments to choose from. But it's one of the last Jeopardy! episodes to air that has us tearing up.On November 5th, 2020, the iconic game show aired as usual. But the post-game chat is when things got emotional. Winner Burt Thakur, who earned $20,400 to become the newest champion, was asked by Trebek if he had any family members back home cheering him on.As the camera panned back to Trebek, he looked almost stunned at the admission, and his impact on his audience young and old was evident. As many touching moments as Alex Trebek left us with, there are plenty of hilarious moments to remember, too. The Jeopardy! host was known for his dry and witty humor, and in one October 2016 episode he really brought it out. In the episode, contestant Susan Cole explains her love of nerdcore hip hop, a genre of music that sprung up at the turn of the millennium thanks to artists like MC Frontalot and MC Chris. It's a style Trebek admits he's never heard of, and he even says it, quote, doesn't sound like fun, but Cole is undeterred. Alex Trebek also knew how to use a joke to support the show's contestants. In 2005, as the show was taping its Tournament of Champions, tensions were reportedly high. Competitors Ken Jennings, Brad Rutter, and Jerome Vered joked that they were all completely pantsless behind their podiums. Trebek was amused by the concept, and decided to join in on the fun.As the Tournament of Champions began, Trebek strode out in his usual jacket, tie, dress shirt, and pocket square, with just boxers, shoes, and dress socks on.Unfortunately for Trebek, the contestants ended up chickening out on their agreement. Trebek demanded the camera reveal all three men wearing pants. Then, ever the good host, he simply strode back offstage while the contestants doubled over with laughter and the audience applauded.Despite how much Trebek enjoyed gently joking with contestants, he still shared plenty of tender moments with them too. One of the most heart-wrenching Jeopardy! moments happened during a 2019 Tournament of Champions episode, which was shot after Trebek shared his cancer diagnosis.Normally during Final Jeopardy, contestants are hunched over their podiums, focusing as they write down their answers. However, as the camera panned over contestant Dhruv Gaur, he just grinned at the audience. Trebek called on Gaur first, noting his smile.Of course, the incorrect answer lost Gaur the remainder of his money, but he earned a place in Jeopardy! lore.Soon, the We Love You Alex' hashtag started trending on Twitter as fans shared their affection for the beloved host. Based on the outpouring of love from fans after Trebek's passing, millions of viewers shared Gaur's sentiments. Trebek's final episode of Jeopardy! will air on Christmas Day, 2020, so get those tissues ready.#AlexTrebekRead Full Article: https://www.thelist.com/275105/one-of-the-alex-trebeks-last-jeopardy-moments-will-bring-you-to-tears/

title: The Truth About Donald And Melania Trump's Only Son
tags: the list|thelist|donald trump|melania trump|donald and melania trump|barron trump|donald trump son|melania trump son|donald trump melania trump son|donald trump only son|melania trump only son|donald trump melania trump barron|donald trump barron trump|melania trump barron trump|barron trump white house|barron trump youngest|barron trump oprah|barron trump slovenian|barron trump school|barron trump little donald|barron trump sneakerhead
description: Love him or hate him, President Donald Trump and his family have capitalized on the reality star-turned-politician's fame. But while most of the Trumps are making headlines, one family member has managed to skirt the spotlight. 14-year-old Barron Trump is the only son of President Trump and the First Lady - and here's what America's First Kid is all about!Barron Trump is one of five children, from Donald's three marriages. Barron's older brothers, Donald Jr. and Eric, are the children of Donald and his first wife, Ivana. Also from the first marriage is Ivanka, who works as an official assistant to the President, while her husband, Jared Kushner, is a senior adviser. Barron's two older brothers often appear in the spotlight due to their leading roles in The Trump Organization. title: Alex Trebek's Last New 'Jeopardy!' Episode to Air This Week With Tribute
tags: [none]
description: The final new Jeopardy! episodes hosted by Alex Trebek will air this week, with highlights that promise to be memorable.The first of the five episodes will air Monday Jan. 4 and start with Trebek's powerful message about the season of giving, producer Sony Pictures Television said in a release Wednesday (30 DEC. 2020).The final episode, on Friday, will conclude with a tribute to the longtime and beloved host. He died of pancreatic cancer on Nov. 8 at age 80.Trebek, who had been candid about his condition, worked up until 10 days before he died, soldiering on despite debilitating treatments and the disease's toll.It was unexpected that the episodes taped in late October would be his final ones, Sony said. Trebek had been fighting the disease for nearly two years.Veteran Jeopardy! champion Ken Jennings will take over as guest host starting on Jan. 11. title: Tabitha From Bewitched Is All Grown up - See the Photos
tags: Tabitha From Bewitched Is All Grown up - See the Photos|tabitha from bewitched|bewitched cast today|tabitha from bewitched is all grown up|tabitha from bewitched today|facts verse|facts verse presents|bewitched cast|bewitched|tabitha from bewitched now|tabitha from bewitched all grown up|see the photos|bewitched behind the scenes|behind the scenes bewitched|bewitched facts|facts about bewitched
description: Bewitched was one of the most popular sitcoms of the 60s and 70s. Audiences and critics alike couldn't get enough of Samantha and Darrin Stephens. The duo began to feel like extended members of our families as we tuned in week after week. Ratings went through the roof. To say that the series was a success is a bit of an understatement. In fact, half a century later it's still re-ruining in syndication all throughout the world.If you're a fan of the show you probably remember little Tabitha, Sam and Darrin's daughter. Her addition marked a major turning point for the story. She very quickly became an essential addition to the cast and won over our hearts with her cute, endearing ways.Although she could be a bit of a handful as well. She started using magic at a young age - including twitching her nose just like her mother. Samantha and Darrin certainly had their hands full. Tabitha was particularly headstrong and needed extra special discipline. Despite her unorthodox upbringing, Tabitha turned out to be a pretty well-adjusted kid.Well, little Tabitha, portrayed by Erin Murphy, is all grown up now, and we have the inside scoop as to what she's been up after all these years. Some child stars wind up having pretty awful lives, but we think that you'll find that Murphy has found her way. Sure, she might not be a huge Hollywood movie start these days, but she certainly has carved out her own path to success.

description: The Beverly Hillbillies is an American sitcom television series broadcast on CBS from 1962 to 1971. The show had an ensemble cast featuring Buddy Ebsen, Irene Ryan, Donna Douglas, and Max Baer Jr. as the Clampetts, a poor backwoods family from the Ozarks region of Arkansas[1] who move to posh Beverly Hills, California after striking oil on their land. The show was produced by Filmways and was created by writer Paul Henning. It was followed by two other Henning-inspired country cousin series on CBS: Petticoat Junction and its spin-off Green Acres, which reversed the rags-to-riches, the country-to-city model of The Beverly Hillbillies. The Beverly Hillbillies ranked among the top 20 most-watched programs on television for eight of its nine seasons, twice ranking as the number one series of the year, with 16 episodes that remain among the 100 most-watched television episodes in history. It accumulated seven Emmy nominations during its run. The series remains in syndicated reruns, and its ongoing popularity spawned a 1993 film remake by 20th Century Fox.Like this content? title: Why Ivanka And Jared Are Already Upsetting Their New Neighbors
tags: nicki swift|nickiswift|ivanka|ivanka trump|trump|jared kushner|donald trump|tom brady|gisele bundchen|adriana lima|don shula|carl icahn|billionaire bunker|ivanka and jared|jared and ivanka|javanka|indian creek country club|insurrection|insurrection at the capitol|politicians|trumps defeat|election aftermath|biscayne bay|indian creek island
description: In the wake of Donald Trump's electoral defeat, rumors are swirling that Ivanka Trump and her husband Jared Kushner are planning to get out of dodge ‚Äî and that their potential new neighbors aren't all that pleased about it.Reportedly, moving trucks have been spotted outside the family's mansion in an upscale area of Washington, D.C., as the couple have purchased an empty Miami lot worth $32 million in the exclusive Indian Creek Village. Residents of the private island, which is also known as the Billionaire Bunker and consists of only 29 homes, include footballer Tom Brady and his supermodel wife Gisele B√ºndchen, supermodel Adriana Lima, former Miami Dolphins coach Don Shula, and billionaire businessman Carl Icahn.But if Trump and Kushner were expecting the residents of Indian Creek to roll out the welcome wagon for their arrival, they may be sorely disappointed. Although anyone with enough money can buy a home or plot on the island, not everyone is able to become a member of the highly exclusive Indian Creek Country Club. And, according to a source at Page Six, Ivanka and Jared are considered persona non grata at the club after the recent insurrection at the Capitol. The source explained:You have to be nominated and make a formal application. But it only takes one member to object against any new member, and many members are objecting particularly after the events at the Capitol on January 6th. [...] The Indian Creek Country Club members are very picky and the word is that Javanka need not apply.Unfortunately for the couple, they seem to have become embroiled in the tumultuous events of early January ‚Äî with Ivanka in particular facing criticism for calling the rioters American patriots. So, while the couple and their children will be free to enjoy their 1.8-acre Miami lot, with its 200 feet of private waterfront, it's doubtful they'll get the chance to enjoy the country club's amenities - which include an 18-hole golf course and a restaurant.But that's not all. With Ivanka and Jared's move to the Sunshine State now in jeopardy, it appears that returning to the concrete jungle might not be an option for them, either. The former New York City residents are allegedly on the outs with the city's elite social scene, with many influential New Yorkers telling The New York Times they can forget about ever returning to the Big Apple. As NYC socialite Jill Kargman told the publication:I have had visions of Ivanka with her thousand-dollar hair and makeup trying to show up at the opera like that and getting ejected. The poetic justice is that coming to New York would put them in a kind of prison already.However, shunning the couple could be a strategic decision made by some in an attempt to appear neutral in the typically Democratic state. A source told Vanity Fair:Everyone with self-respect, a career, morals, respect for democracy, or who doesn't want their friends to shame them both in private and public will steer clear.But the same insider notes they will likely be welcomed back by some - especially those who see the Trumps as their best chance at getting near to power. Another source added:They will probably be welcomed by real estate types and that group of Upper East Side and Palm Beach families that read about themselves. And even in that social scene, the source says:There will always be private dinner parties for them to attend, but they will be the entertainment.And while some may not be too pleased to see Jared Kushner and Ivanka Trump strolling around the block when they eventually finish construction on their Billionaire's Bunker property, others seem less bothered. Even though Page Six notes their future home will take around two years to build, some locals have already been getting chummy with the Kushners. Noting that the residents on the island are largely Republican, an insider revealed:Ivanka and Jared had already been made to feel very welcome on the island. They had received numerous invitations to dine with their future neighbors.And hey, even if they don't manage to get into Indian Creek's Country Club ‚Äî there's always the Trump-brand golf resort nearby.
